{
  "abstract": "Alfisols are the third most important soil order in the world, covering 13.1% of the world area.\r\nIn the semi-arid tropics, Alfisols cover a much larger area of potentially arable and grazable\r\nlands than Vertisols, which have until now received far more attention from ICRISAT\r\nresearchers. About 62% of the world’s Alfisols are located in West Africa and India",
